comments.body:
In commit "validation: pruning for multiple chainstates" (b9ac4f7925e2d9dec67be06fdc2a381532581136)

Would suggest compressing this all down to:

```c++
// Set the end of the prune range to the maximum height which is at least
// MIN_BLOCKS_TO_KEEP blocks away from the chain tip, and is not higher than the
// highest block that is allowed to be pruned according to the caller.
prune_end = std::min(std::max<int>(0, chain_height - MIN_BLOCKS_TO_KEEP), last_prune);
```

Assuming `prune_height` is renamed back to `last_prune` as suggested earlier and made into an int.

